14/08/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government adopted a programme Wednesday (13 August) aimed at improving the country's business climate and making it more attractive to foreign investors. The programme is intended to secure a stable macroeconomic environment, speedy economic reforms and improved infrastructure. It also includes a set of measures to improve the effectiveness of public administration, reduce corruption and accelerate administrative procedures for foreign investors. (MIA - 13/08/03)
